Self-report measures object-80 Value: The RCADS questionnaire/RCADS sub questionnaires.  The RCADS stands for child anxiety and depression rating scale, to assess intensity of the difficulties of low mood and various types of anxiety presentations: separation anxiety, OCD, generalised anxiety, and social anxiety, to help to see severity of the types of difficulties present.
Clinician measures object-81 Value:
The 5Ps model to help to assess how the difficulties developed, e.g the depression. 
The 5Ps model incorporates:
P - presenting difficulty/ or problem e.g the depression 
P - predisposed - what made the young person more vulnerable to the problem (in their life) e.g the depression.
P- precipitate - what led up to the problem e.g the depression, what triggered the problem e.g the depression
Perpetuate - what keeps the problem e.g the depression going 
Protective - what positive things does the young person have in their life to help them to cope.
Further info object-82 Value:
- Parents view of the problem. what help the parents would like: interventions/support
- what help the young person would like: inteventions/goals 
- Information from school/education as to how the young person functions/presents at school
- the young person risk to themself, their risk to others, and their risk from others 
- Opinions of any other professionals/workers currently or previously involved with the young person in and outside of CAMHS services.
- whether there is any involvement from social services, or police, their views, and what the their involvement is or has been.
Treatment object-86 Response: Psychodynamic/Psychoanalytic Psychotherapy
